      • getSequenceNumber

        public int getSequenceNumber()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Provides the sequence number of this license term, unique within the current asset (e.g. 1, 2, 3).

        License terms use a Smint.io sequence number to be unique within the current asset (e.g. 1, 2, 3).

        A sequence number is a positive value. All values below 0 are considered invalid and indicate an unknown value.

        Specified by:
        getSequenceNumber in interface ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Returns:
        the new sequence number or equal to below 0.

      • getExclusivities

        public String[] getExclusivities()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Provides a list of exclusive rights that are granted and on that the restrictions in this instance applies to.

        An exclusivity type defines a scope for all restrictions and allowances in this instance.

        Each value is a simple reading text, valid with the Smint.io platform. Its value is arbitrary and uses mixed cases.

        Non-exhaustive example:

        • any
        • exclusive_usage
        • exclusive_size
        • exclusive_placement
        • exclusive_distribution
        • exclusive_geography
        • exclusive_industry
        • exclusive_language

        Although a known set of values are used, some might be changed and more be added in the near future without any further notice. So implementing classes must support an arbitrary value.

        Specified by:
        getExclusivities in interface ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Returns:
        the enumeration name of exclusivity granted or null.

      • getAllowedLanguages

        public String[] getAllowedLanguages()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Provides a list of allowed languages to use the related asset with.

        Each value is an ISO 639-3 language code. java.util.Locale is not used, as it contains a geographical component, too.

        There is one addition to the ISO 639-3 codes. "any" is used to denote any language. There is not ISO code for that.

        Specified by:
        getAllowedLanguages in interface ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Returns:
        a list of ISO 639-3 values (or "any") or null.

      • getUsageLimits

        public String[] getUsageLimits()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Provides a list of usage limits to apply to the usage of the related asset.

        Each value is a simple reading text, valid with the Smint.io platform. Its value is arbitrary and uses mixed cases. Each value denotes a certain limit upon the usage of the asset.

        Non-exhaustive example: any, quantity_any, quantity_one_copy, quantity_up_to_10_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_25_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_50_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_100_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_250_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_500_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_1000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_2500_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_5000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_10000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_25000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_50000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_100000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_250000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_500000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_1000000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_2000000_total_circulation, quantity_up_to_3000000_total_circulation, display_any, display_up_to_5_displays, display_up_to_10_displays, display_up_to_25_displays, display_up_to_50_displays, display_up_to_100_displays, display_up_to_250_displays, display_up_to_500_displays, copy_any, copy_one_copy, copy_two_copies, copy_three_copies, copy_four_copies, copy_five_copies, copy_up_to_10_copies, copy_up_to_50_copies, copy_up_to_100_copies, copy_up_to_500_copies, copy_up_to_1000_copies, copy_up_to_5000_copies, copy_up_to_10000_copies

        Although a known set of values are used, some might be changed and more be added in the near future without any further notice. So implementing classes must support an arbitrary value.

        Specified by:
        getUsageLimits in interface ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Returns:
        a list of Smint.io enumeration values or null.

      • getToBeUsedUntil

        public OffsetDateTime getToBeUsedUntil()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Provides the date until making use of the related asset for the first time must be started.

        Some content providers prohibit sharding, meaning buying a lot of exclusive content but not making use of it. This behavior would block others from exclusive content without effectively making use of the content itself. Blocking other is the main achievement. So a licensor might require the licensee to make use of the asset before a specific date.

        Specified by:
        getToBeUsedUntil in interface ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Returns:
        the date before this asset must be used for the first time. null if no restriction apply.

      • isEditorialUse

        public Boolean isEditorialUse()
        Description copied from interface: ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Provides a flag that this term restricts the use of the related asset to editorial usage.

        Until a value has been passed to this function, it can not be determined whether the asset is for editorial use only or not. There might be some content provider that do not provide this information on some assets. It simply is impossible to tell. The default assumption and its derived legal action depends on the synchronization target. Smint.io can not give any advise how to handle such content.

        Specified by:
        isEditorialUse in interface ISmintIoLicenseTerm
        Returns:
        Boolean.TRUE in case the term restricts for Editorial Use only and Boolean.FALSE otherwise. If this can not be determined, than null is being returned.
